<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>December 8, 2000.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Server Status Added</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>Well, today was a fun day. I decided I should finally do something with that right hand column. So much studying of php and perl later, I have put up a server status list, just like they have on all the 'big boy' sites.</p><p>At the moment, the script is being called every time someone loads the page, and I need to rework it so it updates periodically. In the meantime, it will just be on the main page of the site, and not on the subsections, so I don't overload the EQ servers with the data requests, hehe.</p><p>Enjoy!</p></FONT></ul>

